Ad Text:
Western Sydney International (Nancy-Bird Walton) Airport is at the heart of the incredible transformation across Western Sydney. WSI will be a 24/7 hub for international, domestic and cargo services, create fantastic career opportunities in Sydney's cultural heartland.

We've reached a major milestone with completion of the terminal and runway, and we're now working towards opening our world class airport later this year. Designed for efficiency and sustainability with state-of-the-art infrastructure and technology, there'll be opportunities for generations to come in Sydney's fastest growing area. We're now looking for passionate people who want to be part of something special - building a legacy for Western Sydney.

About the Opportunity

Reporting to the Integration Manager, this position will contribute to the design and implementation of end-to-end integration solutions using the MuleSoft Anypoint Platform, with a strong focus on CloudHub, Solace PubSub+, Globalscape EFT and Azure DevOps CI/CD pipelines.

The role will work with integration projects that connect SaaS and on-premises systems across the enterprise, while also taking on platform administration responsibilities for critical integration and file transfer platforms.

We're looking for a strategic thinker who can contribute to technical discussions, design scalable integration solutions, and collaborate with the operations teams while ensuring best practices, governance standards, and robust technical documentation are maintained. Experience with Microsoft Fabric and Data Engineering will be considered a strong plus, as the role may evolve to include upskilling and contributions in these areas.

Key responsibilities:

Delivering robust, scalable, and secure MuleSoft-based integration solutions that seamlessly connect diverse systems (e.g., Airport Operational Systems, SaaS applications, and third-party platforms), meeting business requirements and achieving 100% uptime and performance targets.
Establishing and maintaining efficient CI/CD pipelines in Azure DevOps, resulting in no deployment failures, reduced release cycles, and consistent adherence to automated testing and code quality standards.
Proactively managing and optimizing platform administration tasks for MuleSoft CloudHub, Solace PubSub+, and Globalscape EFT, ensuring platform health, timely upgrades, and compliance with security policies, with no unplanned outages or security incidents.
Driving collaboration with stakeholders to produce high-quality technical documentation and reusable integration assets, enabling faster onboarding of team members and reducing integration development time.
Enforcing MuleSoft governance standards and best practices, achieving full compliance in audits and delivering measurable improvements in integration performance, scalability, and maintainability across all projects.
Applying existing experience or proactively upskilling in Microsoft Fabric and Data Engineering to support future initiatives in data integration, analytics, and enterprise data solutions, contributing to the team's evolving capabilities in these areas.


About You

Bachelor's degree in computer science, Information Technology, or related field.
3+ years of enterprise integration experience, including MuleSoft development, with expertise in CloudHub and Anypoint Platform.
Knowledge of API-led connectivity, RESTful services, RAML, and DataWeave.
MuleSoft Certified Developer and/or Platform Architect certifications.
Experience with Solace PubSub+ for messaging is a plus.
Experience with Azure DevOps or other DevOps tools for CI/CD automation.
Experience with platform administration for MuleSoft CloudHub, Solace PubSub+, and Globalscape EFT.
Knowledge of license management, user access provisioning, and platform upgrades.
Knowledge of integration patterns, security protocols (e.g., OAuth2, SAML), and performance monitoring in MuleSoft CloudHub.
Experience with Microsoft Fabric and Data Engineering will be considered a strong plus.
Proven ability to produce high-quality technical documentation.
Excellent problem-solving, communication, and stakeholder management skills.
Experience working in Agile/Scrum methodologies.
Experience in proactively monitoring and troubleshooting MuleSoft and Solace platforms, performing performance tuning, capacity planning, and incident resolution.
Expertise in implementing RBAC, managing certificates, licenses, and ensuring compliance with enterprise security standards.
Demonstrates a commitment to maintaining platform stability, scalability, and performance through proactive monitoring and best practices.
Works effectively with enterprise architects, analysts, and developers to align platform capabilities with technical and business requirements.
Ensures integration platforms adhere to governance, compliance, and security frameworks.
Adaptability in Hybrid Environments - Comfortable managing systems that span cloud and on-premises infrastructure.
Enthusiastic about building new skills in emerging technologies such as Microsoft Fabric and data engineering.

What we offer:

At WSI you're not just joining a team - you're becoming part of a community that thrives on purpose, passion and possibility.

We're building a culture that brings out the best in people, empowering every individual to grow, contribute and shine. Whether you're just starting out or looking to take your career to the next level, we offer experiences that unlock your full potential.

There's some great benefits such as discounts on health insurance, travel, gyms and pools plus novated car leasing and the ability to purchase additional leave.

Our values power everything we do:

Safety Because nothing matters more.
Heart Our passion drives us in everything we do.
Striving To be different and better.
Achieving together We make it happen with collaboration

Proudly working on Dharug land, we reflect the vibrant diversity of Western Sydney and welcome people from all backgrounds and abilities to be part of our journey. Please let us know if you require any adjustments to the application or recruitment process.

How To Apply

Please submit your application via the link or to make an enquiry email Thao Vu at WSI tvu@wsiairport.com.au

To apply for this role, you must already have the right to lawfully work and live in Australia.

If you're our preferred candidate, you'll be requested to undergo background and medical checks.

For more information explore the WSI website https://wsiairport.com.au or our Facebook, Instagram or LinkedIn pages.

Company description:



Capgemini is a global business and technology transformation partner, helping organisations to accelerate their dual transition to a digital and sustainable world, while creating tangible impact for enterprises and society. It is a responsible and diverse group of 340,000 team members in more than 50 countries. With its strong over 55-year heritage, Capgemini is trusted by its clients to unlock the value of technology to address the entire breadth of their business needs. It delivers end-to-end services and solutions leveraging strengths from strategy and design to engineering, all fuelled by its market leading capabilities in AI, cloud and data, combined with its deep industry expertise and partner ecosystem. The Group reported 2023 global revenues of 22.5 billion Euro.



Job description:



Cloud & Custom Applications (CCA) combine design and technology with modern delivery methodologies to deliver experience oriented, scalable, sustainable and secure enterprise solutions. We are tech savvy consultants on a journey to deliver innovation and expertise to our clients. Join a collaborative team that is solution focused and empower each other to be their best.

We are well known for our work on modern web applications; we are involved at all stages of the software delivery lifecycle from ideation through implementation to deployment. We're also strong on integrations, IoT, cloud migrations and app modernisation.

Role and responsibilities

We are seeking an experienced ACE Engineer to join our high-performing integration team. This role requires a seasoned professional who can hit the ground running in a fast-paced financial services environment, delivering robust integration solutions using IBM App Connect Enterprise and Azure cloud technologies. The successful candidate will play a key role in designing and implementing enterprise-level integrations that support our core banking operations and digital transformation initiatives.

Key Responsibilities

• Design, develop, and maintain integration flows using IBM App Connect Enterprise v12/v13 (ACE/IIB)
• Build and manage SOAP/REST APIs, message queues, and event-driven integrations
• Collaborate with architects and BA's to translate business requirements into robust technical solutions
• Implement comprehensive error handling, logging, and monitoring for all integration flows
• Support CI/CD pipelines, deployment automation, and version control processes
• Ensure all solutions comply with security, governance, and performance standards
• Create technical documentation, sequence diagrams, and present designs to stakeholders



Profile description:



Required Technical Skills:

• Proficiency in IBM ACE/IIB development with Java, XSLT, and message modelling (DFDL, XMLNSC)
• Strong experience with IBM MQ support and development
• Linux operating system experience
• Working knowledge of Java, XML, JSON, DFDL, SQL, and scripting languages
• Experience with cloud-hosted ACE configurations, particularly Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS)


Preferred Qualifications:
• Financial services or banking industry experience (beneficial but not required)
• Azure cloud platform experience
• Strong documentation and presentation skills
• Self-motivated with strong sense of ownership and responsibility



We offer:



We recognise the significance of flexible work arrangements to provide support. Be it remote work, or flexible work hours, you will get an environment to maintain healthy work life balance.

At the heart of our mission is your career growth. Our array of career growth programs and diverse professions are crafted to support you in exploring a world of opportunities.

Equip yourself with valuable certifications in the latest technologies such as AWS and Microsoft Azure.

So many job ads talk about "accountability" - but here, it's all about opportunity.

As the project architect, creator, and strategist, you’ll lead engagements end-to-end. You’ll be trusted to run delivery while tapping into internal and external support as needed. It’s a high-trust culture that rewards autonomy and craftsmanship.

Most projects are Sydney-based, with some travel to Melbourne and Singapore.

This is not a notebook-hacking role. We’re looking for someone who builds clean, reproducible, and well-organised production-grade code—combining the rigour of engineering with the insight of data science.

Ideal Candidate:

3–5 years' experience as a Data Scientist with a Data Engineering edge
Consulting (Big 4,, MBB) and Financial Services experience
Proficient in Python (R, SAS, etc. are not core to this environment)
Practical experience with classical ML libraries: XGBoost, NLTK, Scikit-learn, etc.
Solid background in data engineering workflows
A disciplined approach to coding- clean architecture, version control, and documentation are second nature
This strategic consultancy offers a flexible, adult working environment where delivery quality matters more than hours logged. Most projects are open source and cloud-native, with a strong commercial edge.
Why join?


High-performance bonus program with proven track record
Strong global brand and high-impact projects
Flexibility in working style and location
Sound like you? Contact Ronny at ronny@theonset.com.au for a confidential discussion.

Job Title: Lead Full-Stack Embedded & IoT Software Engineer
Ad Text:
About us

PlasmaLeap Technologies is a globally recognised Australian clean-chemicals company reinventing how the world makes molecules. We’re decarbonising heavy industry by putting clean, distributed chemical production in the hands of communities themselves. Our proprietary plasma reactors use renewable electricity, air and water to produce green fertilisers and fuels, creating a scalable, commercially viable pathway to net-zero that strengthens food security and bypasses fragile, fossil-fuel global supply chains entirely. 

If you want to build deep tech that solves climate and food security in the same breath, and you want to do it at speed, with urgency, with purpose, and with people who are actually executing not just talking about it, then you’ll fit right in. 

The opportunity

You’ll own software end-to-end across the stack. This is a hands-on role for someone who enjoys owning and developing new systems from scratch, fast!

Embedded (PIC MCU)

- Develop and maintain firmware on PIC microcontrollers

- Implement and debug device communications: I2C, SPI, UART, RS-485, CAN

- Build robust drivers for sensors/actuators, ADC/DAC interfaces, timing, interrupts, watchdogs

- Design fault-tolerant state machines for safety-critical behaviour (interlocks, failsafes, graceful shutdown)

- Support manufacturing bring-up: flashing tools, test hooks, factory calibration, board validation

- Bring up new PCBs/modules with the electronics team: validate power rails, clocks, comms buses

Edge/Linux (rack/controller level)

Build services/applications on Linux devices (SBC/industrial PCs):

- control orchestration

- logging and data capture

- configuration management

- remote command & diagnostics

OTA updates

- Interface with modules over RS-485/CAN and expose clean APIs upwards

- Package and deploy reliably (systemd services, containers if useful)

IoT / Cloud integration

- Implement/maintain MQTT telemetry and command channels (QoS, retained messages, session handling)

- Device identity/provisioning, secure comms (certs/keys), and fleet operations basics

- Integrate data into dashboards/alerts (Grafana/Prometheus, InfluxDB, cloud equivalents, etc.)

- Build internal tools that help engineers and operators see what’s happening across devices

What we’re looking for:

Strong hands-on embedded experience (C/C++) on microcontrollers; comfortable with interrupts, peripherals, memory constraints
Real hardware interfacing and debugging experience with at least I2C + RS-485 + CAN (or can demonstrate equivalent depth)
Linux development experience (C/C++/Rust/Python/Go—pick your weapon) including system services and deployment
Experience with MQTT and IoT patterns (telemetry, remote commands, device provisioning)
Proven ability to debug across boundaries: firmware ↔ hardware ↔ Linux ↔ network
Experience shipping industrial devices or field-deployed fleets
OTA update experience
Comfortable working in a fast, iterative environment with physical prototypes

Why you should join PlasmaLeap Technologies:

We Move Fast - Build, test, and learn outside your comfort zone alongside curious, driven teammates. 

We Make an Impact - Work on meaningful challenges that decarbonise industry and improve global food security. 

We’re Getting Recognised – PlasmaLeap is earning global recognition through international awards and world-class investors backing us from multiple continents,

We Own It - Every team member has a voice and takes real ownership in a culture of experimentation as we rapidly develop, prototype and scale our technology.  

We Celebrate Wins - Enjoy fun, engaging company events while working hard on ambitious goals. 

We Reward Talent – To build the best, you have to employ the best. Competitive salary, equity, and coverage for training and conferences.

Making a difference isn’t just our purpose, it’s what motivates our people every day. For us, work is not about ticking a box. It’s about knowing that it matters. We make a meaningful difference every day by making it easier for our customers to focus on what matters in their lives. 

The Integration team builds software that connects MMS systems to third parties and internal consumers.

Here’s how you will make a difference in this role… 

In your Integration Engineering role, you will design, build, and support integration solutions that enable secure and reliable data exchange between MMS systems, third-party providers, and internal consumer platforms.

You can work hybrid or remotely depending on your preferences from Melbourne, Brisbane or Sydney and surrounds. You will be required to come into the office in one of the major cities listed above for workshops on occasion.

The successful candidate will have experience delivering and supporting integration solutions in a complex .NET and Azure-based corporate environment. They will be comfortable working across modern cloud services and legacy technologies, engaging with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.

At MMS clear expectations help our people Be the Difference.  Your key responsibilities in this role will include: 

Experience with Azure cloud services, including APIM, Azure Functions, App Services, Logic Apps and Service Bus

Experience designing and building REST APIs using modern code design patterns, including Clean Architecture

Experience building CI/CD pipelines and knowledge of DevOps practices using GitHub and Azure DevOps

Cloud reliability and SRE concepts (observability, distributed tracing, resilience patterns) 

Knowledge of automated testing of backend systems

Knowledge of EF Core, SQL Server and Azure Cosmos DB

Exposure or interest in building software using AI tools such as Github Copilot or Claude Code

Knowledge of Azure Event Hubs and Event Grid Concepts will be advantageous but not essential

 To be considered for this role you will have: 

Strong verbal and written English communication skills 

5+ years delivering backend or integration solutions in a medium-to-large enterprise

Comfortable contributing to both project delivery and production support activities 

Ability to collaborate effectively with architects, platform engineers, testers, business analysts, and business stakeholders 

 What we can offer you:

Novated leasing benefits and discounts

12 weeks paid parental leave and access to our Parents Portal

Comprehensive learning and development opportunities to support your career growth

Sonder digital wellbeing platform, providing personalised support 24/7, plus annual flu vaccinations

Default Income Protection Insurance reimbursed for members of the MMS Default Super Fund

Exempt Employee Share Plan

 Embracing our value of Everyone Matters we hold a collective commitment to foster an environment where all differences are valued and respected. 

We encourage individuals from all backgrounds including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, those caring for someone or living with a disability, LGBTQIA+ and culturally diverse applicants to apply.

We embrace hybrid working and welcome conversations about flexibility. 

 Please note all successful candidates will undergo background checks (including criminal history and ASIC checks) and an NDIS Workers Screening Check if appropriate.  All information provided will be treated confidentially. 

We acknowledge Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples as the Traditional Custodians of the lands where we live, learn and work.

If you identify as a person living with disability and require adjustments to our recruitment process, please contact us at mmsgrouprecruitment@mmsg.com.au

About CORTO

We are CORTO, a cutting-edge software company dedicated to revolutionizing the legal industry. Our mission is to empower legal practitioners with AI-driven solutions that streamline their workflow, boost productivity, and provide more efficient client service.

Our team of AI experts and engineers collaborate to develop intelligent software tailored to the unique needs of lawyers, paralegals, and legal assistants.

Our innovative AI solutions automate routine tasks, simplify document management, and enhance decision-making, allowing legal professionals to focus on what they do best—providing expert legal counsel.

What you’ll do

We are looking for a talented Integrations Manager to own and grow CORTO’s third-party integration ecosystem. In this role, you will manage external developers and partners who build applications and integrations that call CORTO’s APIs, ensuring high-quality, secure, and scalable integrations.

Reporting to the Head of Backend Engineering, you will sit at the intersection of engineering, product, and commercial teams—shaping integration standards, improving developer experience, and ensuring integrations deliver real value to customers.

This is a hands-on role that combines technical understanding, stakeholder management, and operational excellence.

To make this happen you will:

This is an incredible opportunity to be part of an engineering team building the next generation of our products. The day to day will include:

Owning the operational health and performance of CORTO’s third-party integrations and developer ecosystem
Onboarding new integrations
Liaising with CTO to provide reports on performance and usages of integrations
Owning and maintaining CORTO’s API documentation
Providing technical support for developers and other stakeholders
Reviewing new and updated integrations
Collecting feedback from stakeholders and communicating improvements required to the Development team
Approving / rejecting application reviews
Build strong internal and external relationships through clear, professional written and verbal communication
Working closely with key business decision makers and cross-functional development and testing teams to offer guidance and advice on what solutions will best fit the business needs
Reviewing and improving integrations team workflows
The candidate will be required to be a good cultural fit for our team as values and behaviours are important within our teams

What you’ll bring:

Experience in working in a fast-paced Agile environment
Experience in gathering requirements from stakeholders
Experience in creating technical documentation specifications
Experience in working on tech support tasks
Familiarity with REST services and APIs
Strong delivery focus to complete tasks within schedule and quality standards
Strong stakeholder management skills

Even better if you have;

Database experience (mySQL, MSSQL and / or DynamoDB)
Knowledgeable on best practices for both UI and UX development
Knowledge of AWS products
Knowledge of OAuth and Auth0
Knowledge of LEAP products
Experience in using Atlassian products
Experience working with json / yaml specifications

You are the type of person who has

Strong problem-solving skills, analysis skills and attention to detail
Strong verbal and written skills
Enjoys working in fast-paced environments

CORTO is an inclusive, people-first company committed to breaking down institutional barriers that keep people from reaching their potential. If you meet some, but not all the requirements above, we encourage you to still submit your application.

Why join CORTO?

Your work matters. We solve real world problems that improve and support local, everyday law firms. So they can do their best work for the people in the communities they serve.
Make an impact. You won’t be another ‘cog in the wheel’ here. We give full trust and autonomy for you to be heard, to work on big & complex projects – and to make a real difference.
Work with a group of authentic, passionate people who love what they do.
Well-funded and global. CORTO is part ofATI – one of the largest international LegalTech companies.
Flexible and hybrid working. We engage, share, and collaborate on ideas and workflows.
Career and learning opportunities; we move fast and need smart people to get us where we're going. We are a scaling business and looking for people who want to grow with us.
Have fun with us. Celebrations. Socials. Sports teams. Access to sailing and yacht events.
We value your well-being - Wellness focus with additional time off, gym membership and other perks.
Fast-paced tech environment, if we don't disrupt ourselves someone else will do it!
Access to LEAP Home - a program unique to LEAP to support you in buying your primary residence.
